---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'UK Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/uk/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Ireland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ireland' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'ukFit', header: 'UK Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£380-550/mo', ukFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£350-500/mo', ukFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£320-460/mo', ukFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£300-440/mo', ukFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'NHS (National Health Service)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Free (resident)', ukFit: 'Full Access' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '£320-500', annual: '£3,840-6,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '£450-680', annual: '£5,400-8,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '£600-900', annual: '£7,200-10,800' },
  { category: 'UK Private Insurance (PMI)', monthly: '£200-500', annual: '£2,400-6,000' },
  { category: 'NHS', monthly: 'Free', annual: 'Tax-funded' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in the UK 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in the UK. NHS access, private options, visa requirements, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in the UK"
  subheadline="The UK offers free NHS healthcare for residents plus world-class private options—but immigration rules require careful planning."
  heroImage="/images/countries/uk-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/bupa-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose the UK</h2>
  <p>
    The UK offers English-speaking culture, rich history, excellent healthcare, and strong connections to Europe and North America. For seniors from Commonwealth countries or with British heritage, there's often a cultural familiarity that eases the transition.
  </p>

  <p>
    London provides world-class culture and medical facilities. The Cotswolds and Bath offer quintessential English countryside. Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands appeal to those seeking dramatic landscapes. Cornwall and Devon provide milder coastal climates.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> NHS is free for residents; ranked highly globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> £2,000-4,000/month outside London; London much higher</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild but rainy; cold winters in Scotland</li>
      <li><strong>Public Transport:</strong> Good trains; excellent in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Post-Brexit:</strong> No longer in EU; different visa requirements</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">UK's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    The National Health Service (NHS) provides free healthcare to all UK residents. GPs (general practitioners) are your first point of contact, referring to specialists as needed. Emergency care is always free, including for visitors.
  </p>

  <p>
    While the NHS is comprehensive, wait times for non-urgent procedures can be long. Many seniors supplement with Private Medical Insurance (PMI) for faster access to specialists, choice of consultants, and private hospital rooms.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">NHS Wait Times</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      NHS waiting lists have increased in recent years. Non-urgent specialist referrals can take months; some procedures have 12+ month waits. Private insurance provides faster access for those who can afford it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Post-Brexit, UK immigration requires specific visa routes:
  </p>

  <h3>Ancestry Visa</h3>
  <p>
    If you have a UK-born grandparent, you may qualify for a 5-year ancestry visa with right to work and live in the UK. After 5 years, you can apply for Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR).
  </p>

  <h3>Family Visa</h3>
  <p>
    If you have a British spouse, partner, or close family members settled in the UK, you may qualify for a family visa.
  </p>

  <h3>Global Talent / Investor Visas</h3>
  <p>
    The Innovator Founder visa requires a significant business investment. These aren't typical retirement routes but can provide a pathway.
  </p>

  <h3>Healthcare Surcharge</h3>
  <p>
    Most visa applicants must pay the Immigration Health Surcharge (IHS) of £1,035/year, which grants full NHS access during your visa period.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs depend on your visa status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive coverage may be required before IHS kicks in</li>
    <li><strong>IHS payers:</strong> Full NHS access included in surcharge</li>
    <li><strong>Settled status/ILR:</strong> Full NHS access; may add PMI for faster care</li>
    <li><strong>Visitors:</strong> GHIC/EHIC (EU citizens) or travel insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for UK</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Most seniors moving to the UK use NHS as primary care and add private insurance (PMI) for faster specialist access and private hospital options. International insurance provides flexibility for travel and potential return to home country.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in the UK, both international and local providers offer strong options:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for the UK</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> UK-based company, excellent local network, highest entry age (79)</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong UK presence, good international flexibility</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> Good European network, competitive UK pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Moratorium underwriting available for pre-existing conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for the UK.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    The UK offers a range of insurance options from free NHS to premium private coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHS primary:</strong> Use NHS for routine care; private for specialists</li>
    <li><strong>Six-week NHS option:</strong> Some PMI policies cover only if NHS wait exceeds 6 weeks</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> £500-1,000 excess significantly reduces PMI premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient exclusion:</strong> Excluding outpatient care from PMI reduces cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Australian with UK Ancestry, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> British-born grandfather qualifies for ancestry visa. Moving to Edinburgh.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pay IHS for NHS access. Add BUPA PMI for private specialist access when needed.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IHS £1,035/year + PMI ~£350/month. Full NHS + private options.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Moving for Family, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Adult daughter lives in London. Applying for family visa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa application. After IHS enrollment, keep Cigna for US coverage during visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially £450/month; reduce coverage once NHS enrolled (UK excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Retiree, 75</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> British wife, returning to UK after 30 years in Canada. Has heart condition.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Family visa through spouse. NHS covers pre-existing condition. BUPA PMI with moratorium for non-cardiac private care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IHS + BUPA ~£500/month. NHS covers cardiac care fully.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How long are NHS waiting times really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        It varies by procedure and location. Emergency and urgent care is immediate. Routine GP appointments typically within 1-2 weeks. Specialist referrals: 4-18 weeks. Some surgeries: 6-18 months. Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland have separate NHS systems with varying wait times.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to the UK from outside the EU?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Post-Brexit, there's no retirement visa per se. You need a qualifying route: ancestry (UK grandparent), family connection, or investment. Without these, long-term residence is challenging. Some retirees use visitor status (6 months) with periodic exits, but this doesn't provide NHS access.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about prescriptions on the NHS?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        England charges £9.90 per prescription item (2026). However, people over 60 get ALL prescriptions free. Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland also provide free prescriptions for all ages.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is private medical insurance worth it?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For seniors wanting faster access to specialists or specific consultants, yes. PMI provides choice, shorter waits, and private hospital rooms. For routine and emergency care, NHS is excellent. Many combine both: NHS for most care, PMI for when speed matters.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for the UK.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with UK authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
